HEADWORD: Pulvillo
<hw>Pul*vil"lo</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Pulvil</er>.]</ety>
<def>A kind of perfume in the form of a powder, formerly much used, --
often in little bags.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Smells of incense, ambergris, and <qex>pulvillios</qex>.</q>
